<section class="village-season" id="village">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title text-center">The Village Season</h2>
    <p class="lead text-center text-muted">
      Three months per year. A real container with rhythm, not a festival.
    </p>

    <div class="season-intro">
      <p>
        Every December through February, southern hemisphere summer, Rosemary Dream runs
        as a village gathering. A curated group of builders, founders, artists, researchers,
        and community-minded people converge for a season of deep work, shared life, and
        mutual support. The days have structure. The structure creates freedom.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="rhythm-grid">
      <div class="rhythm-block">
        <h3 class="rhythm-time">Mornings</h3>
        <p class="rhythm-label">Movement, Ocean, Breath, Strength</p>
        <p class="rhythm-description">
          Daily movement classes, surf sessions on world-class breaks,
          jungle hikes, and morning breathwork. The day begins in the body.
          Howler monkeys move through the canopy above the terrace.
          Salt air. Green light. Strong coffee.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rhythm-block">
        <h3 class="rhythm-time">Midday</h3>
        <p class="rhythm-label">Deep Work, Structured Coworking, Goal Setting</p>
        <p class="rhythm-description">
          People have real projects here. The space holds focus. Structured
          coworking blocks, shared goal-setting rituals, and accountability
          partnerships. You make more progress in a week here than in a month
          of scattered solo work back home.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rhythm-block">
        <h3 class="rhythm-time">Evenings</h3>
        <p class="rhythm-label">Authentic Relating, Shared Meals, Creative Play</p>
        <p class="rhythm-description">
          Long communal tables. Conversations that go where they need to go.
          Salons, ecstatic dance hosted at the venue, music, creative play.
          Authentic relating practices that build the kind of trust you cannot
          manufacture in a Slack channel.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="season-promise">
      <p>
        The core promise: belonging, purpose, shared creativity, and real momentum
        on meaningful work. This is not a networking event. It is a village.
        The people you meet here become long-term collaborators, friends, and
        co-conspirators in building a better way to work and live.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .village-season {
    background: var(--color-white);
  }

  .section-title {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .lead {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .season-intro {
    max-width: 650px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--spacing-lg);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .season-intro p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .rhythm-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--spacing-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .rhythm-block {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    padding: var(--spacing-md);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-top: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  .rhythm-time {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .rhythm-label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .rhythm-description {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .season-promise {
    max-width: 650px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: var(--spacing-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .season-promise p {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
</style>
